  "text": "factor that compensates for the different number of samples in each class [CITATION_1] . As a result, the mapping b b is a reduced rank transformation matrix [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] , which could be used to project a test data x tst 2 R mÂ1 onto an l-dimensional space. Note that directly minimizing (1) avoids the small-sample-size problem by not using the covariance matrices. After it projects the samples to the output space, we need a simple step to infer the class labels. LDA maximizes inter-class variance, while minimizing the intra-class variance, in the mapped space. Thus, we expect that in the mapped space, same-class samples to be closer to each other. The class labels could, therefore, be simply determined using a k-NN strategy.",
